    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 140\u00b0C/ 120\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 1, then wash your <strong>shredded kale</strong> and pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add the <strong>shredded kale</strong> to a large baking tray (or two!) with a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Give the shredded kale a good mix up, then put the tray[s] in the oven for 25-30 min or until crispy \u2013 this is your <strong>crispy 'seaweed'</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-salt-and-pepper-tofu-with-rice-and-crispy-seaweed/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 225ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [450ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-salt-and-pepper-tofu-with-rice-and-crispy-seaweed/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, drain your <strong>tofu</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Chop your <strong>tofu</strong> into large bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped tofu</strong> to a bowl with <strong>half</strong> your <strong>soy sauce </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and set aside to marinate</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-salt-and-pepper-tofu-with-rice-and-crispy-seaweed/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and slice (don't chop!) <strong>half </strong>your <strong>garlic cloves </strong>(save the rest for later!)</p><p>Slice your <strong>red chilli[es] </strong>finely</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-salt-and-pepper-tofu-with-rice-and-crispy-seaweed/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>five-spice mix </strong>and your <strong>cornflour </strong>to the bowl with the <strong>marinated tofu </strong>and give everything a good mix up until the tofu is fully coated</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once the pan is very hot, add the <strong>coated tofu</strong> and cook for 5-6 min, turning occasionally until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-salt-and-pepper-tofu-with-rice-and-crispy-seaweed/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the tofu is crispy, add the <strong>onion wedges </strong>and <strong>chopped pepper </strong>to the pan with the <strong>sliced garlic </strong>and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>sliced chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Season with a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and cook for 4-5 min further or until the vegetables are beginning to soften \u2013 this is your <strong>salt & pepper tofu</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-salt-and-pepper-tofu-with-rice-and-crispy-seaweed/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Grate the <strong>remaining garlic</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>grated garlic </strong>with your <strong>rice vinegar</strong>, <strong>remaining soy sauce</strong>, <strong>remaining sliced chilli </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>in a small bowl \u2013 this is your <strong>dipping sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-salt-and-pepper-tofu-with-rice-and-crispy-seaweed/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>salt & pepper tofu </strong>with the <strong>cooked rice</strong>, <strong>crispy 'seaweed'</strong> and <strong>dipping sauce </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
